
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `foo2zjs-wrapper` yek dastoor baraye tabdil dade-haye raster shode az Ghostscript be format ZjStream printer-ha ast. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ta printer-haye GDI ra az rah-andazi konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `-z` --> 🚀 Eslahe rang-ha baraye chaph behtare rang-ha.
    🔹 `-r <resolution>` --> 🎯 Ta'een deghat chape (dpi). Mesal: `-r300` ya `-r600`.
    🔹 `-g` --> 🎨 Taghire range chap shodan be range khakestari (grayscale).
    🔹 `-u <username>` --> 👤 Namayeshe username (Agar username mored niaz bashad).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ foo2zjs-wrapper < input.ps > output.zjs

    🔹 Tabdil file PostScript `input.ps` be format `output.zjs`.

    $ foo2zjs-wrapper -r600 < input.ps > output.zjs

    🔹 Tabdil file PostScript `input.ps` ba deghate 600 dpi be format `output.zjs`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ foo2zjs-wrapper -z < input.ps | lp

    🔹 Tabdil file PostScript `input.ps` ba eslahe rang-ha va ezafe kardane an be saf chape.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `foo2zjs-wrapper` command is a wrapper that converts rasterized data from Ghostscript into the ZjStream format suitable for certain printers, mainly GDI printers. It helps to drive these printers.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `-z` --> 🚀 Color correction for better color printing.
    🔹 `-r <resolution>` --> 🎯 Specify the printing resolution (dpi). Example: `-r300` or `-r600`.
    🔹 `-g` --> 🎨 Force grayscale printing.
    🔹 `-u <username>` --> 👤 Set username (If username needed).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ foo2zjs-wrapper < input.ps > output.zjs

    🔹 Converts the PostScript file `input.ps` to `output.zjs` format.

    $ foo2zjs-wrapper -r600 < input.ps > output.zjs

    🔹 Converts the PostScript file `input.ps` to `output.zjs` format with a resolution of 600 dpi.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ foo2zjs-wrapper -z < input.ps | lp

    🔹 Converts the PostScript file `input.ps` with color correction and pipes it to the printing system.
